sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as NotebookWebhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant KubeflowCtrl as Kubeflow Controller<br/>Creates StatefulSet
    participant ODHCtrl as ODH Controller<br/>Reconciles Resources
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthSvc as {notebook}-tls Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NotebookPod as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,NotebookPod: Flow 1: Notebook Creation with OAuth Injection

    User->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutating Webhook Call<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS (mTLS)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Check annotation<br/>inject-oauth=true
    Webhook->>Webhook: Inject OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>Add culling stop annotation
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Return Mutated Spec

    K8sAPI->>KubeflowCtrl: Notebook CR Created
    KubeflowCtrl->>KubeflowCtrl: Create StatefulSet<br/>with OAuth sidecar

    K8sAPI->>ODHCtrl: Watch Event: Notebook Created
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS Reencrypt
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Service ({notebook}-tls)<br/>443/TCP → oauth-proxy
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount<br/>with OAuth redirect annotation
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Secret (oauth-config)<br/>Cookie secret (random base64)
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Secret ({notebook}-tls)<br/>Service CA triggers cert creation
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>Allow 8443/TCP from anywhere
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Remove culling stop annotation<br/>Unlock notebook start

    Note over User,NotebookPod: Flow 2: User Accesses OAuth-Enabled Notebook

    User->>Router: HTTPS GET /notebook-url<br/>443/TCP TLS1.2+ (no auth yet)
    Router->>OAuthSvc: Forward (Reencrypt)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    OAuthSvc->>OAuthProxy: Route to Pod<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS

    OAuthProxy->>OAuthProxy: Check for valid cookie
    OAuthProxy-->>User: HTTP 302 Redirect to OAuth

    User->>OAuthServer: OAuth Login Flow<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    OAuthServer-->>User: OAuth Token

    User->>Router: HTTPS GET with OAuth Token<br/>443/TCP
    Router->>OAuthSvc: Forward<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    OAuthSvc->>OAuthProxy: Request with Token<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS

    OAuthProxy->>OAuthServer: Validate Token<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    OAuthServer-->>OAuthProxy: Token Valid

    OAuthProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>verb=get, resource=notebooks<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>OAuthProxy: Authorized: true

    OAuthProxy->>OAuthProxy: Set encrypted cookie<br/>Expiry: 24h
    OAuthProxy->>NotebookPod: HTTP GET /<br/>8888/TCP (localhost)
    NotebookPod-->>OAuthProxy: JupyterLab UI
    OAuthProxy-->>OAuthSvc: HTTPS Response
    OAuthSvc-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>User: Notebook UI (authenticated)

    Note over User,NotebookPod: Flow 3: Controller Reconciles Notebook (Manual Route Change)

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl patch Route<br/>Manual modification
    K8sAPI->>ODHCtrl: Watch Event: Route Updated
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: GET Route current spec<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    ODHCtrl->>ODHCtrl: Compare with desired state
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: PATCH Route (restore spec)<br/>Retry with exponential backoff
    K8sAPI-->>ODHCtrl: Route reconciled
